# ── Day 91 — NEW LLM PROVIDERS (OpenRouter + SambaNova + Cerebras) ──
# All three are OpenAI-compatible (chat.completions.create), so we can
# reuse the openai-style request shape we already use for Groq. The
# fallback chain in master_analyst._call_llm is now:
#
#     Groq → Cerebras → SambaNova → OpenRouter → Gemini
#
# Cerebras + SambaNova are FIRST in the fallback (after Groq) because:
#   - Both offer free tier with generous TPD (much higher than Groq)
#   - Both serve Llama 3.1 8B / 70B — same model family we already use
#   - Cerebras is the fastest inference available (low latency = fast
#     cycles = more trades analyzed per hour)
# OpenRouter is later in the chain because it has paid + free models
# mixed; we use it as a "catch-all" fallback that can route to many
# different models if all the direct-provider keys are exhausted.

