# ── P1 audit fix: MT5 broker timezone offset ──────────────────
# Many MT5 brokers (IC Markets, Pepperstone, Exness, FXTM) return
# bar OPEN time in broker SERVER TIME rather than true UTC. The
# broker server time is commonly GMT+2 in winter / GMT+3 in summer
# (the so-called "FX broker time" used to keep daily candles
# aligned with NY close).
#
# When that happens, the fetcher receives wall-clock seconds that
# are 2-3 hours AHEAD of true UTC, and pd.to_datetime(unit='s')
# silently treats them as UTC — producing timestamps that look
# "in the future" relative to UTC `now`. This is the exact root
# cause of the "10540s left on M15 candle" / FUTURE_BAR bug.
#
# Set this to your broker's GMT offset (in hours). Examples:
#   MT5_BROKER_TZ_OFFSET_HOURS=0   broker server IS UTC (default)
#   MT5_BROKER_TZ_OFFSET_HOURS=2   broker is GMT+2 (winter)
#   MT5_BROKER_TZ_OFFSET_HOURS=3   broker is GMT+3 (summer / DST)
#
# The log shows "[MT5] Bar timestamps (UTC): first=... last=..."
# after each fetch — if `last` is in the FUTURE relative to UTC
# now, INCREASE this value. If `last` is in the PAST within one
# timeframe interval, the fix is working.
MT5_BROKER_TZ_OFFSET_HOURS=3

# ── P3 audit fix: initial balance for position sizing ─────────
# Set this to your real live MT5 account balance so position
# sizing is correct from the FIRST trade (not after the first
# _sync_balance() call). Eliminates the "drift=891.6%" log spam.
INITIAL_BALANCE_USD=99159.93